metadata.name: Reading a book #887
metadata.description:
The formal structure of a book is beautiful by itself, but its aesthetic is the tacit atmosphere within which events take place in a story.

The WebGL real-time animation sets up an initial grid based on the fxhash. The grid cells get subdivided into another grid and the resulting cells become filled with pixels in color (~33%) or black and white (~66%).
The colored pixels come in 3 different coloring styles.
- Big Palette (~49%)
- Small Palette (~49%)
- Monochrome [b/w] (~2%)
4 noise algorithms modify the pixels of selected grid cells while at the same time 4 reset algorithms reassemble the initial image. The selected cells switch over time.

metadata.name: Parrot #52
metadata.description:
Generative art, written with Vanilla JS & 6 layers of png is used (Tree branch, Toes, Parrot body, Beak, Nose jewel, eye glass, Gold Pendant , scarf, Tie, Cap, VR Head set). 
- Pixel based Image processing 
- Color inversion is achieved by subtracting each RGB color value from 255
- Algorithm reads each 6 layers of the parrot in memory and apply Color inversion
In the objective of decorating the squeaky birdy for all seasons I started layering with various traits and accessories. While the computed combinations surprised me with a trans-seasonal wardrobe for the birdy which are unique.
Few mix-matches like Nose jewel, Eye glass, Cap, VR glass remains cute.

metadata.name: E R E B U S #297
metadata.description:
Fragments of minds

Our daily life is filled with automatisms, habits that make our comfort zone. Then one day an event occurs that touches us deeply. We step out of our comfort zone, an internal emotional tornado is unleashed in our consciousness. This work tries to illustrate this flow of passion, this emotional violence on the fabric of daily life.

About features.
There are 3 random characteristics:

1. Latent state of mind
This feature correspond to the lines in the background. ‘Healthy’ is the most frequent, and the other types appear more rarely (’Psychotic’ is really rare).

2. Crystallization

This feature corresponds to the strength of the flow of the passion in our mind. Probability : ‘Normal’ = 77%, ‘Strong’ = 33%.

3. Disturbance
The disturbance rate is ’Low’ (frequent), or ‘High’ (rare).

When a work is collected, a process of synchronicity is triggered. Synchronicity is a process of randomness that allows us to communicate with our unconscious (psychological paradigm) or with the hidden forces of the universe (spiritual paradigm). The rarer an image is, the more it represents an exceptional psychic state.

To print a high resolution image (resolution is 6400*6400px.), press [p].
To print a screen resolution image, right-clic then ‘save image’.

This artwork celebrate the anniversary of FxHash - Happy Birthday little baby :-)
50% of primary sales are donate to the Processing Foundation (thank you for making my days better).

Artwork by @GenerativePunk.

metadata.description:

In this Digital Artwork, I have used a combination of CG and artificial intelligence, as well as layers of texture to convey a visual pleasure to the viewer. The random combination of these layers creates an image that an artist may not be able to achieve by himself.

metadata.name: ProtoByte: Scyphozoa.01 #1
metadata.description:
Scyphozoa.01 is the alpha release built with my new ProtoByte.ts library.

ProtoByte is a Verlet Integration-based creative coding framework designed to simulate and render organic, aesthetic structures and behaviors. It combines physics simulation with artistic visualization, offering versatile tools for creating dynamic, whimsically lifelike forms and interactions in 3D.

ProtoByte.ts
Release notes:

As I begin to release #genart projects like Scyphozoa.01, and soon enough the ProtoByte.ts library itself, I thought it would be useful to share my thoughts and hopes for the project. 

I plan to vary minor and major releases in alignment with library development. This drop reflects a minor (though quite significant personally) internal release. Minor releases will generally have more affordable pricing and larger editions.

Project Goals:
1.  Release a fun, distinct and highly useable library, with advanced behavior for creative coding that supports existing core libs such as @threejs, @p5jsArt, @processingOrg, @babylonjs.

2. Develop and nurture a userbase that both create with and contribute to the overall ProtoByte.ts project.

3. Develop supporting pedagogy to continue my 30 year odyssey in #creativecoding. 

4. Continue to contribute to the mission for increased adoption, growth and value of Web3 as a major creative space/art marketplace.

metadata.name: EDDY #56
metadata.description:
An eddy is a circular movement of water counter to a main current. It reminds me of innovations in art, like a small countercurrent to the mainstream, surfacing new techniques and aesthetics. 

I hope that EDDY will brighten your days with its playful swirl of colors, inspired by the sea, the sky, the birds, and post-impressionist paintings.

Keyboard Controls:
[F] Fill the window.
[S] Save the current view in live mode as an image (default 1125x1500px).
[1] [2] [4] [6] Change resolution, 1.5K to 9K.
[R] Reverse course.

Made with p5js and shaders.

Created by elsif, 2022.12.

metadata.name: Orchard #334
metadata.description:
A natural media rendering of a fruit tree during one of the four seasons. Sometimes, you'll catch it at night - with lights strung on the tree!

The amount of color in spring and fall, snow in winter, fruit on and off the tree will all vary. There are four spring bloom palettes, four trunk colors, and seven types of fruit. 

Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1000x1000px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

To render a variation at a new size, open live view and append '?size=#' to the end of the URL. The new size may be from 100 to 3,000. This version will not be a 1:1 match to your edition but will have all of the same features.

metadata.description:
I often find myself submerged in neuroses that obstruct my stream of reasoning. This collection is a reminder: look closely and it will be possible to identify what is the result of trauma. I try to translate each experience into art. Any experience.

Texture was defined with layers of noise, background is consciousness, the layer representing neurosis is multiplied above.

Full-screen / F11 for better experience.
